This is Perl module HTML::Lint::Pluggable.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - HTML::Lint::Pluggable

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
HTML::Lint::Pluggable:

    $ cpanm HTML::Lint::Pluggable

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf HTML-Lint-Pluggable-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd HTML-Lint-Pluggable-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

HTML::Lint::Pluggable documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc HTML::Lint::Pluggable

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

